-/# DOCKER DAY ONE 
* Ubuntu Server
Launch an Instance in Ubuntu
Connect the instance (ssh)

1. sudo apt-get update //update packeges
2. sudo apt-get install docker.io -y  // install docker
3. sudo systemctl docker start // start docker
4. sudo service docker status  //check status
4. sudo systemctl status docker.service // check status
5. sudo su //become the super user
6. docker search nginx // search for image in docker
7. docker pull nginx //pull nginx image
8. docker image ls //to check list of images
9. docker run [image name or image id] // run docker in forgraund
10. exit // stop running docker
11. docker ps -a // list of container
12. docker run -d --name containerName nginx [nginx becuase we are using it] // create and name container
13. docker exec -it <containerId> or <containerName> /bin/bash  // execute container
14. cd /usr/share/nginx/html  //go to html directory
15. curl ://localhost  //run html page
16. apt update  //update apt in html directory
17. apt install nano  //install nano in html directory
18. nano hello.html  //create html page [other than index.html] 
19. curl localhost/hello.html  //execute html page [Foreground]

** To Run In Background **
1.   docker run -d --name mynginx -p 80:80 nginx


